: 1774618706:0;Create a Python music player using mpv.\
\
Requirements:\
1. Support audio EQ with 3 controls:\
 - Bass\
 - Mid\
 - Treble\
\
2. Add 3 presets:\
 - Rock\
 - Pop\
 - Soft\
\
3. Each preset should set default EQ values.\
\
4. When user selects a preset:\
 - Update bass, mid, treble values\
 - Display current preset name\
\
5. When user manually changes bass, mid, or treble:\
 - Automatically change preset name to "Custom"\
\
6. Allow real-time update using mpv (no restart required).\
\
7. Add keyboard controls:\
 - r = Rock\
 - p = Pop\
 - s = Soft\
 - b/B = decrease/increase bass\
 - m/M = decrease/increase mid\
 - t/T = decrease/increase treble\
\
8. Show current status:\
 - Preset name\
 - Bass / Mid / Treble values\
\
Use Python and subprocess or mpv IPC.
